DOCTYPE Declaration :- (DTD)
********************************
It is an instruction to the browser.
It is not a tag
It will that which version of markup language we are using in the browser.

HTML 4
In HTML 4 we have 3 doctype declaration(dtd)
1) HTML 4.01 Strict
  In That page i cannot use <frames>,<font>,<center> tags

2) HTML 4.01 Transistinal
   I cannot use only <frames>
   
3) HTML 4.01 frameset
   Every tag will work
        
Now days we are going to use HTML 5 doctype
<!DOCTYPE html>
        
*******************************************************
HTML Meta tags:-
****************
syntax:

<meta name="" content="">

Note:
*****
we should write the meta tags compulsary in the <head> section only

Meta gives the information about the webpage to the search engines (google , bing , etc...)

1)Title of the page
<meta name="title" content="Durga Soft Solutions">

2) Description :-

<meta name="description" content="......">

3) Keywords

<meta name="keywords" content="telugu songs,telugu movies">

4) Author Information

<meta name="Author" name="Praneeth">


        
        